label: A4B2C6D16E_cF232_227_e_c_f_eg_b-001
title: $H5_{6}$ [Tychite, Na$_{6}$Mg$_{2}$SO$_{4}$(CO$_{3}$)$_{4}$)] Structure ({\em Obsolete})
comments:
This is the original structure determined by (Shiba, 1931) and given the designation $H5_{6}$ in (Hermann, 1937). (Schmidt, 2006) showed that the true structure is \href{current_web_home_dir/A4B2C6D16E_cF232_203_e_c_f_eg_b-001}{in space group $Fd\overline{3}$ \#203}, however the two structures are very similar, and a displacement of the oxygen atoms by less than 1{\AA} brings the two structures into agreement. 
 (Hermann, 1937) gives the chemical formula as Na$_{6}$Mg$_{2}$SO$_{4}$(CO$_{3}$)$_{2}$, but the given Wyckoff positions are in agreement with the correct formula, Na$_{6}$Mg$_{2}$SO$_{4}$(CO$_{3}$)$_{4}$.
